    <summary>Represents a virtual display.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>Represents a virtual display. The content of a virtual display is rendered to a
            <c>android.view.Surface</c> that you must provide to <c>DisplayManager#createVirtualDisplay
            createVirtualDisplay()</c>.</para>
      <para>Because a virtual display renders to a surface provided by the application, it will be
            released automatically when the process terminates and all remaining windows on it will
            be forcibly removed.  However, you should also explicitly call <c>#release</c> when
            you're done with it.</para>
      <para>
        <format type="text/html">
          <a href="https://developer.android.com/reference/android/hardware/display/VirtualDisplay" title="Reference documentation">Java documentation for <code>android.hardware.display.VirtualDisplay</code>.</a>
        </format>
      </para>
